HEADWORD: Trichogyne
<hw>Trich"o*gyne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Gr.
<grk>tri`x</grk>, <grk>tricho`s</grk>, hair + <?/ woman, female.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The slender, hairlike cell which receives the
fertilizing particles, or antherozoids, in red seaweeds.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Trich`o*gyn"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

